Project 1: Sales Data Analysis (Exploratory Data Analysis)
Title

Exploratory Data Analysis of Retail Sales to Identify Business Insights

Problem Statement

Retail businesses generate large volumes of transactional data, but without proper analysis, it is difficult to identify trends, seasonal patterns, and high-performing products. The objective of this project is to perform Exploratory Data Analysis (EDA) on a retail sales dataset to uncover meaningful insights that can support business decision-making such as inventory planning, marketing strategy, and revenue optimization.

Dataset / Inputs

The dataset contains transactional sales records with the following features:

Order Date

Product Category

Product Name

Sales Amount

Quantity Sold

Region / City

Customer Segment

The data was provided in CSV format and loaded using Python.

Methodology

The project was implemented using Python with libraries such as Pandas, NumPy, Matplotlib, and Seaborn.

Steps performed:

Data Loading and Inspection

Loaded dataset using Pandas

Checked data types, missing values, and duplicates

Data Cleaning

Handled missing values

Removed duplicate records

Converted date columns to datetime format

Feature Engineering

Extracted Month and Year from Order Date

Created revenue aggregates by category and region

Exploratory Analysis

Monthly sales trends

Sales by product category

Top-performing products

Regional performance comparison

Data Visualization

Line plots for time trends

Bar charts for category comparison

Heatmaps for monthly performance

Outputs

The analysis produced:

Monthly revenue trend visualization

Top 10 products by sales

Category-wise revenue distribution

Region-wise sales performance dashboard
